</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1368D0306FFC3FF20747FC88D8B1D" blockId="10.[144,759,1043,1126]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FF20747FCB398B53" box="[144,269,1043,1064]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species is dedicated to Dr Ramon Margalef, an eminent ecologist who recently passed away, in gratitude for all his stimulating work.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1368D0306FFC3FF2074F8CB8D8B9D" blockId="10.[144,759,1171,1254]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FF2074F8CB328BD2" box="[144,262,1172,1193]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Species distinguished by the number of chaetigers and the size of the chaetae in relation to the size of the branchiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1368D0306FFC3FF207578CEA98E62" blockId="10.[144,759,1299,1903]" lastBlockId="10.[806,1421,198,281]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FF207578CB2C8A52" box="[144,280,1300,1321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Description:</emphasis>
Body fusiform, small, grooved ventrally and laterally, with 22 chaetigers (
<typeStatus id="54B5882F0306FFC3FD9D755EC8A68A33" box="[557,658,1330,1352]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
), mostly 22–24 (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FF5A753DCB548A1C" box="[234,352,1361,1383]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
). 
<typeStatus id="54B5882F0306FFC3FEC9753DCBD78A1C" box="[377,483,1361,1383]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Holotype</typeStatus>
: 3.2-mm long (ranging from 3.0 to 
<quantity id="4CF69B680306FFC3FEA27503CB538AFE" box="[274,359,1391,1413]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="3.4">3.4 mm</quantity>
in 
<typeStatus id="54B5882F0306FFC3FE3C751CC8348AFE" box="[396,512,1392,1413]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paratypes</typeStatus>
, similar length in the rest of specimens), 0.32-mm wide (ranging from 
<quantity id="4CF69B680306FFC3FD7675E2CB218AB9" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.32" valueMin="0.28">0.28 to 0.32 mm</quantity>
in 
<typeStatus id="54B5882F0306FFC3FEF475C1CB8D8AB9" box="[324,441,1453,1474]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">paratypes</typeStatus>
). Prostomium with acuminate tip. Two large nuchal organs located laterally on prostomium (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FE827586CBB3897B" box="[306,391,1514,1536]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
), eyespots absent. Branchiae: cirriform, small, laterally ciliated, present from chaetiger 2 to 20, shortest in first chaetigers. Ciliary bands distributed on every segment, starting on chaetiger 2 (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FE9B7608CBB48901" box="[299,384,1636,1658]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), one ciliary band observed at parapodial level. Between two consecutive parapodia, another ciliary band is observed dorsally, and two additional ones are observed ventrally (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FDC576ACC8D889AD" box="[629,748,1728,1750]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4A–C</figureCitation>
). Parapodia occur as rounded lobes. No recognizable cirri. Lateral organ present in the middle of every parapodial lobe (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FEE67770CB998849" box="[342,429,1820,1842]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Chaetae: all capillary and hirsute (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FF477756CB78882B" box="[247,332,1850,1872]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
), with several chaetae longer than the prostomium width. Anal tube: cylindrical (maximum length about 
<quantity id="4CF69B680306FFC3FBF370AACE9D8FA0" box="[1091,1193,198,219]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="0.14">0.14 mm</quantity>
), terminating in six subequal papillae, with the two ventralmost ones larger than the others (
<figureCitation id="13352A080306FFC3FB8C716FCEA58E62" box="[1084,1169,259,281]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="11.[164,243,1672,1691]" captionTargetBox="[164,1444,196,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[164,1444,196,1643]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 4. Ophelina margaleffi sp. nov. A, general view. B, lateral view of anterior region. C, mid-region parapodia showing cirriform branchiae and ciliary bands. D, lateral organ observed in the middle of every parapodial lobe (from left to right dorsoventral orientation). E, hirsute capillary chaetae. F, pygidium with six subequal papillae. Scale bars: A, 1 mm; B, C, 100 Mm; F, 50 Mm; E, 10 Mm; and D, 5 Mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5445998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5445998/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1368D0306FFC3FC967124CED28A4A" blockId="10.[806,1422,328,1329]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FC967124C9938E26" box="[806,935,328,349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Discussion:</emphasis>
From all the known 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FB747124CFB98E25" box="[1220,1421,328,350]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FB747124CF198E26" box="[1220,1325,328,349]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Ophelina</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(about 60 species), 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FBB1710BCEB58E00" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1958" box="[1025,1153,358,380]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FBB1710BCEB58E00" box="[1025,1153,358,380]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FC9671E9C98B8EE1" authority="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili, 2009" authorityName="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili" authorityYear="2009" box="[806,959,389,410]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="margaleffi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FC9671E9C98B8EE1" box="[806,959,389,410]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. margaleffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24957E40306FFC3FC7B71E9CE128EE1" box="[971,1062,389,410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, especially in its size and the number of chaetigers. Unfortunately, the 
<typeStatus id="54B5882F0306FFC3FAA071C8CF758EC2" box="[1296,1345,420,441]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
material of this species could not be located in Scandinavian museums, but 
<specimenCount id="9D08FD040306FFC3FBBD718DCE938E8C" box="[1037,1191,481,503]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="generic">12 specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FB7E718DCF7B8E8D" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1958" box="[1230,1359,481,502]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FB7E718DCF7B8E8D" box="[1230,1359,481,502]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Langesundsfjord, 
<collectingCountry id="F319761D0306FFC3FC47726CCE648D6E" box="[1015,1104,512,533]" name="Norway" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Norway</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity id="4CF69B680306FFC3FBD37193CE9D8D6E" box="[1123,1193,511,533]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0699999999999998" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="m" value="107.0">107 m</quantity>
depth) collected in 2003, close to the 
<typeStatus id="54B5882F0306FFC3FBBE7272CE0B8D48" box="[1038,1087,542,563]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
locality, were available for study. The specimens from Lagesundsfjord were clearly different to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FBA07237CE9D8D0B" authority="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili, 2009" authorityName="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili" authorityYear="2009" box="[1040,1193,603,624]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="margaleffi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FBA07237CE9D8D0B" box="[1040,1193,603,624]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. margaleffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24957E40306FFC3FB067230CF208D0A" box="[1206,1300,604,625]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: they had distinct eyes on the prostomium, the chaetae of the parapodia were shorter and not hirsute, and were present in lower numbers, and its nuchal organs were very apparent, similar to that observed in the original illustrations in the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FB0A7298CF0A8C72" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1958" box="[1210,1342,756,777]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FB0A7298CF0A8C72" box="[1210,1342,756,777]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Støp- Bøwitz, 1958). The specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FB2C737FCF058C53" authority="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili, 2009" authorityName="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili" authorityYear="2009" box="[1180,1329,787,808]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="margaleffi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FB2C737FCF058C53" box="[1180,1329,787,808]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. margaleffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24957E40306FFC3FA88737FCFBA8C53" box="[1336,1422,787,808]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were also compared, using SEM, with several specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FBAD733CCEE68C1E" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1958" box="[1053,1234,848,870]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FBAD733CCE038C1E" box="[1053,1079,848,869]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FBC4733CCEE68C1E" box="[1140,1234,848,869]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
obtained from muddy sediments at a depth of 
<quantity id="4CF69B680306FFC3FB197302CED58CFF" box="[1193,1249,878,900]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="m" value="65.0">65 m</quantity>
in the Bay of Roses (Catalan Mediterranean region). The 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FA8173E1C95E8CBA" authority="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili, 2009" authorityName="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili" authorityYear="2009" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="margaleffi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FA8173E1C95E8CBA" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. margaleffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24957E40306FFC3FCC573C0C9F98CBA" box="[885,973,940,961]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
specimens clearly differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FC9673A7C9F18CA4" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1958" box="[806,965,970,992]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FC9673A7C9748C9B" box="[806,832,971,992]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FCD773A6C9F18CA4" box="[871,965,970,991]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in the Bay of Roses, but the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FAC373A7C99F8C85" authorityName="Stop-Bowitz" authorityYear="1958" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FAC373A7CFB98C9B" box="[1395,1421,971,992]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O.</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FCFD7385C99F8C85" box="[845,939,1001,1022]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from the Bay of Roses were similar to those from Langesundsfjord (eyes on the prostomium, shorter, non-hirsute chaetae, and no ciliary bands on the body). The anal funnel structure is quite similar in both species. Our observations and measurements, using a light microscope, on 126 individuals showed that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E4D0E0306FFC3FBA974CDCE848BCE" authority="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili, 2009" authorityName="Sardá &amp; Gil &amp; Taboada &amp; Gili" authorityYear="2009" box="[1049,1200,1184,1206]" class="Polychaeta" family="Opheliidae" genus="Ophelina" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="margaleffi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AEA9F0306FFC3FBA974CDCE848BCE" box="[1049,1200,1184,1206]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">O. margaleffi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24957E40306FFC3FB0974CDCF248BCD" box="[1209,1296,1185,1206]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
never had more than 24 chaetigers, and that even for small individuals (10–14 chaetigers), the length of the chaetae clearly surpassed the width of the prostomium and the length of its branchiae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1368D0306FFC3FC1D7501CF328AF9" blockId="10.[941,1286,1389,1410]" box="[941,1286,1389,1410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<collectionCode id="ED1FAE480306FFC3FC1D7501CE378AF9" box="[941,1027,1389,1410]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">FAMILY</collectionCode>
